                <note rend="inline" type="source">822.796/204: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Long</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-08-10T15:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 10, 1940—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>108. Your 179, August 8, 6 p.m. For your strictly confidential information the
                    Department hopes to have arrangements effected in <pb facs="0854" n="842"
                        xml:id="pg_842"/> a few days so that adequate funds will be available for
                    the liquidation of Sedta and the solution of other phases of the general
                    problem.… I expect to summon the Ecuadoran Ambassador within the next few days
                    and to have a frank discussion with him<note n="17" xml:id="d974fn1">The
                        Assistant Chief of the Division of the American Republics (Briggs) spoke at
                        length with the Ecuadoran Ambassador (Alfaro) on August 24 on Mr. Welles’
                        behalf.</note> …pointing out that this Government is cooperating
                    wholeheartedly with Ecuador as evidenced by numerous projects for the execution
                    of which our assistance has been obtained. We feel, particularly in view of this
                    cooperation and the very cordial relations existing between the two Governments,
                    as well as the national defense factors involved, Ecuador should be willing to
                    do its part.</p>
                <p>As soon as funds are definitely available, we shall telegraph our ideas
                    concerning the next steps to be taken.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
